headline: A Few High-Yield Savings Accounts Still Pay 5%. Where to Find Them.
summary: It’s gotten a lot harder to spot online savings accounts that pay 5%.  Earlier this year, it was relatively easy to find high-yield savings accounts, with the benchmark federal-funds rate at its highest level in more than a decade.  Since then, the Fed has cut the rate by three-quarters of a percentage point to a range of 4.5% to 4.75%.
